1. Download nodejs from https://nodejs.org/en/download/
2. Install nodejs as an administrator.
3. Open command promt and set application folder path. 
    > Change the directory using CD command
    > The current directory would expect the source folder
4. Install angular cli using command $ 'npm i -g @angular/cli latest'
5. To execute the application use $ 'ng serve --o' command (This command will run the application by opening a default browser)

Refernce Video Link : https://www.screencast.com/t/PIZQ7p4L6QKZ


